  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">DEC COVID-19 Appeal Phase II - Preparedness for the COVID-19 epidemic in Idleb, North-west Syria</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Phase II of the DEC COVID-19 Response is a continuation of Phase 1, which ends 31st January 2021. In summary, Phase II aims to continue supporting vulnerable communities and local health facilities to respond effectively to COVID-19 in Idleb (NW Syria) through the following:
 1. Access to COVID-19 preventative supplies and adequate knowledge to prevent COVID-19 transmission
 2. COVID-19 preventative messaging through Community Health Workers (CHWs) and social media
 3. Continued support to health systems and facilities to have increased capacity for infection prevention and control (IPV) and treatment of suspected COVID-19 cases, particularly through Jisr As-Shugour hospital
 4. Rehabilitation of sanitation facilities in health facilities.</narrative>
  </description>
